<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> VI!!! GIVE THE KNIGHT CLASSES A BREAK!!!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
SK epic requires a rare drop from Cazic Thule himself, who was upgraded in difficulty a few months ago. (in addition to other annoying things)<br>
<br>
Paladin epic requires a rare drop off of a cleric dragon (Vox or Gore, possibly a few others), who now are incredibly difficult to kill. (in addition to 3 sub-epics, all quested. Ghoulbane, Soulfire, and Fiery Avenger... and then you have to work on Fiery Defender. Yes, I realize that Ghoulbane and Soulfire aren't exactly epic to get, but they both have bottlenecks and rare spawns/low drop rates... Ghoulbane has a rare drop each off of &quot;a goblin&quot; in butcher, &quot;a skeleton&quot; in Najena, and &quot;a crazed ghoul&quot; in Unrest. Soulfire you have to camp forever for Xicotl, kill Lucan (good luck getting enough folks who want to hose Freeport faction), and do some tedious side-tasks.)<br>
<br>
Warriors, while not exactly a &quot;knight&quot; in any race, are considered by many to be a knight class, so I'll mention them too. &quot;Green scale&quot; and &quot;mediocre ratio,&quot; enough said for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/utarskxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarskXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Xev Diplomat</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/02 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epics</span><hr size=1> Ya know the epics that suck the most? It can narrowed down to one type:<br>
<br>
Melee epics that don't have haste effects.<br>
<br>
The rogue/monk/ranger ones shine because they come with 40% haste. Actually, the monkey one is different cos it's a hand slot replacement, but anyway.. <br>
<br>
Look at the weapons:<br>
<br>
Ragebringer: 15/25<br>
Swiftwind: 13/21<br>
<br>
Yeah, they both have nice epic-level stats, but there's better baseline weapons out there in the game than that. The dmg/dly ratio on both of those is nice enough, when compared to Kunark weapons. But we're no in Kunark anymore. The dmg/dly game has moved on from there.<br>
<br>
But haste doesn't change. The haste cap is still 100% (give or take a bardsong or two) So once you got yourself a dragon-class haste item, you don't need anything else.<br>
<br>
The melee epics that people say suck are the ones without the haste - because without haste, the only thing to rate it by is the weapon stats, and that's what has advanced since Kunark.<br>
<br>
Yeah, the taunt on the War epic red blade is nice, but it would be even nicer if the blue blade gave haste, instead of some stat buffs that you don't need at that level, because 4 times out of 5 you're going to have a Shaman with you, especially when raiding.<br>
<br>
If Ragebringer *and* Swiftwind didn't have that 40% haste, people would be saying that they're outclassed these days as well, especially with Luclin. <p>--
